4:
Lemme go, ya little brat! Or else the
hostages are gonna—
14:
Finishing up right now... But we
shouldn't lose focus. Watch my back
for me, will yah?
22:
Look at these stock prices! Surely
they rise in salute of your heroic
deeds!
26:
Yeah, well... We're still not pulling in
the results you want combat-wise.
30:
Have you taken a look online?
Everyone's saying those guys are
the real heroes.
34:
Those security robots? I suppose
they have been rather popular lately.
36:
But that just makes your job all the
more important.
40:
Anyway, think fast, kids! I've got
another job for you. I'll forward the
details, so get to it!
45: This is the place in the report, right?
55:
I was wondering when you would
finally show up. Unfortunately, you're
too late.
66:
Huh? Do you two know each other?
Ah, have you worked together
before?
71:
Are you insane?! I'm nowhere near
her level! You can't even compare
us!
75:
You're looking at Noxel Group's
strongest troubleshooter, the
second generation of the legendary
Themis!
79:
And I'm familiar with you as well...
Nate of PBC.
87:
I understand that you're merely an
idol, but if you're going play at being
a hero, I would prefer if you at least
act the part.
94:
I-I'm not pretending, I really am a
hero—
97:
Do you think the people whose lives
you've endangered would call you
that?
101:
I've looked into your activities up
until now, and I noticed a lot of
unnecessary damage and injuries.
104:
If you ended up killing someone, do
you think all will be forgiven if you
just tell their families you were
"trying your very best"?
113:
Remember that your unsightly
behavior reflects on all of us.
118:
You sure know a lot about Nate. Did
you look her up yourself?
121:
I make sure to research all the
troubleshooters in any districts that
overlap with my own. Imposters
tend to stick out, that's all.
123:
You need the resolve and will of a
hero to BE a hero. Showing off your
powers will only lead to disaster.
129:
That naïve nature of yours won't get
you very far in this world...
134:
Sorry... Maybe I shouldn't have said
anything.
138:
What are you apologizing for?
Besides... Everything she said was
true.
147:
Sounds like you ran into a little
trouble with one of our competitors.
150:
You make it sound so serious. We
didn't even exchange blows.
152:
I heard you were the one who
approached them.
155:
I'll admit I had a few harsh words for
her, but that's nothing new. It
happens all the time between
troubleshooters.
157:
This is a vital time for our plan. Try to
avoid starting unnecessary conflicts.
162:
Well, this has to do with another
company, but one of their districts
has reported a crime rate higher
than they can deal with.
165:
I see... Sounds like you're entering
the final stages, then.
167:
Are you sure you don't want to join
us?
169:
I appreciate the prosthetics and
battle systems you provided me, but—
172:
Understood. Participation is by no
means mandatory.
174:
However, remember that our
company always has the city's best
interests in mind.
177:
How frightening. It sounds like
they've amassed a lot of power.
184:
Those eyes of hers... She seemed so
annoyed with... everything.
